  "prompt": "What are some of the funniest movies you've ever seen?",
  "response": "Humor is highly subjective, but here are some movies that are widely considered to be hilarious:\n\n1. **\"Monty Python and the Holy Grail\" (1975)**\n   - A classic British comedy about King Arthur and his knights, filled with absurd humor and iconic scenes like the \"Black Knight\" and the \"Holy Hand Grenade of Antioch.\"\n\n2. **\"The Big Lebowski\" (1998)**\n   - Directed by the Coen Brothers, this film follows the laid-back \"Dude\" as he gets mistaken for a millionaire and embroiled in a complex kidnapping scheme. It's packed with quotable lines and bizarre characters.\n\n3. **\"Airplane!\" (1980)**\n   - A spoof of disaster films, this movie is known for its rapid-fire gags and slapstick humor. Famous for lines like \"Don't call me Shirley\" and scenes involving a jive-talking passenger.\n\n4. **\"Superbad\" (2007)**\n   - A coming-of-age comedy about two high school friends trying to have a legendary night before they graduate. It's crude, raunchy, and filled with memorable performances, especially by Jonah Hill and Michael Cera.\n\n5. **\"Anchorman: The Legend of Ron Burgundy\" (2004)**\n   - Will Ferrell stars as the pompous 1970s news anchor Ron Burgundy, delivering absurd news reports and navigating the hilarious dynamics of his news team.\n\n6. **\"Borat: Cultural Learnings of America for Make Benefit Glorious Nation of Kazakhstan\" (2006)**\n   - Sacha Baron Cohen's mockumentary follows the Kazakh journalist Borat as he travels across the U.S., creating awkward and often hilarious interactions with unsuspecting Americans.\n\n7. **\"Blazing Saddles\" (1974)**\n   - Mel Brooks' satirical take on Western films is filled with slapstick humor, racial satire, and memorable characters like Sheriff Bart and the Waco Kid.\n\n8. **\"The Hangover\" (2009)**\n   - A group of friends wake up in Las Vegas with no memory of the previous night and must piece together what happened while searching for their missing friend. It's filled with outrageous situations and laugh-out-loud moments.\n\n9. **\"Dumb and Dumber\" (1994)**\n   - Jim Carrey and Jeff Daniels star as two dim-witted friends on a cross-country trip to return a briefcase full of money. Their antics and idiocy provide endless laughs.\n\n10. **\"Step Brothers\" (2008)**\n    - Will Ferrell and John C. Reilly play grown men who are forced to live together as stepbrothers, leading to childish pranks and ridiculous situations that somehow endear them to audiences.\n\nThese movies offer a mix of slapstick, satire, and absurd humor that has resonated with many comedy fans. Of course, humor is subjective, so your mileage may vary!",
